video.title: Doctor Who
video.synopsis: An updated incarnation of everybody's favorite time-traveling Doctor sets about fighting nefarious aliens and other foes in this epic sci fi series.

episodes.synopsis: Department store clerk Rose Tyler meets the mysterious Doctor when he rescues her from a squad of killer mannequins.
episodes.title: Rose

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Rose board the TARDIS and travel to the year 5 billion on the eve of Earth's apocalypse.
episodes.title: The End of the World

episodes.synopsis: Traveling to the year 1869, the Doctor and Rose investigate the origins of a blue gas that brings the corpses in a funeral parlor back to life.
episodes.title: The Unquiet Dead

episodes.synopsis: Rose and the Doctor return to the present day and witness the crash of an alien aircraft into the Thames.
episodes.title: Aliens of London

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor, Rose and Parliament official Harriet Jones discover the motive behind the alien crash-landing but are trapped inside 10 Downing Street.
episodes.title: World War Three

episodes.synopsis: Beneath the salt flats of Utah, the Doctor meets an eccentric collector of alien artifacts and comes face-to-face with an old enemy.
episodes.title: Dalek

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor, Rose and Adam visit the year 200,000, where the Earth's largest broadcast station, Satellite 5, uses mind control over its viewers.
episodes.title: The Long Game

episodes.synopsis: When Rose alters the course of events and saves her father, she creates a time paradox that unleashes deadly creatures.
episodes.title: Father's Day

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Rose chase a strange metal cylinder to 1941 wartime London, where homeless kids are terrorized by a gas-masked unearthly child.
episodes.title: The Empty Child

episodes.synopsis: A growing army of gas-masked zombies threatens to spread the Child's plague unless the Doctor, Rose and charming con man Captain Jack can stop them.
episodes.title: The Doctor Dances

episodes.synopsis: While in present-day Cardiff to recharge the TARDIS, the Doctor encounters an enemy he thought was dead.
episodes.title: Boom Town

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor, Rose and Jack are unwillingly transported into a popular -- but deadly -- reality game show.
episodes.title: Bad Wolf

episodes.synopsis: With the Daleks' numbers rejuvenated, the Time War rages, and the Doctor will have to make difficult choices and sacrifices to save lives.
episodes.title: The Parting of the Ways

episodes.synopsis: Rose struggles to overcome her mistrust of the newly regenerated Doctor to help her defeat a malevolent alien that threatens all life on Earth.
episodes.title: The Christmas Invasion

episodes.synopsis: A distress call brings the Doctor to a posh New Earth hospital, which holds the cure to every known disease and a hidden evil villainess.
episodes.title: New Earth

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Rose go back in time to 19th-century Britain, where a ravenous werewolf and monk assassins threaten Queen Victoria's life.
episodes.title: Tooth and Claw

episodes.synopsis: When the Krillitanes exploit students to obtain ultimate power, the Doctor and Rose come to the rescue; the TARDIS gets a new crew mate.
episodes.title: School Reunion

episodes.synopsis: In 1700s France, sinister clockwork droids from the future attack Madame de Pompadour and her royal court at Versailles.
episodes.title: The Girl in the Fireplace

episodes.synopsis: A malfunction with the TARDIS leaves the Doctor, Rose and Mickey stranded within a parallel universe, where fascism rules Earth.
episodes.title: Rise of the Cybermen

episodes.synopsis: Invading Cybermen seize control of London and begin a hideous conversion on the city's population.
episodes.title: The Age of Steel

episodes.synopsis: The festivities surrounding Queen Elizabeth II's royal coronation are in danger of ruin when reports roll in of monsters in the streets.
episodes.title: The Idiot's Lantern

episodes.synopsis: Rose and the Doctor are stranded on a dangerous planet orbiting a black hole. The situation worsens when an ancient entity awakens below the surface.
episodes.title: The Impossible Planet

episodes.synopsis: Rose fights for her life against the Ood on a planet about to collapse, and a confrontation with the Pit forces the Doctor to question his values.
episodes.title: The Satan Pit

episodes.synopsis: A man obsessed with the Doctor, Rose and their enigmatic blue box is connected with a powerful villain who turns his obsession into a nightmare.
episodes.title: Love & Monsters

episodes.synopsis: When everyday children in 2012 London repeatedly vanish into thin air, the Doctor pays a house call to a suburban girl with horrific powers.
episodes.title: Fear Her

episodes.synopsis: As the Doctor, Rose and Jackie launch an investigation of the Torchwood Tower, Earth is threatened with a global invasion of an unspeakable power.
episodes.title: Army of Ghosts

episodes.synopsis: Earth is the unfortunate battleground between the Cybermen and the Daleks, while a terror beyond imagination emerges from below Torchwood Tower.
episodes.title: Doomsday

episodes.synopsis: Donna's Christmas Eve wedding plans are dashed when she finds herself on the TARDIS and the Doctor scrambles to return her in time for the nuptials.
episodes.title: The Runaway Bride

episodes.synopsis: Medical student Martha Jones thinks she's seen it all... until the day she and her entire hospital are transported to the moon.
episodes.title: Smith and Jones

episodes.synopsis: Martha and the Doctor travel to 1599 England, where they discover that the malevolent Carrionites have William Shakespeare under their spell.
episodes.title: The Shakespeare Code

episodes.synopsis: Carjackers abduct Martha while she and the Doctor are visiting New Earth of the distant future.
episodes.title: Gridlock

episodes.synopsis: When people inexplicably vanish from the New York City streets, the Doctor discovers that the Daleks and bloodthirsty Pig Men have invaded.
episodes.title: Daleks in Manhattan

episodes.synopsis: To build a Dalek empire in 1930s New York City, Sec, a Dalek-human hybrid, launches an attack on humanity.
episodes.title: Evolution of the Daleks

episodes.synopsis: Martha visits her family in modern-day London, where the mad professor Lazarus experiments with age reversal and finds monstrous side effects.
episodes.title: The Lazarus Experiment

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Martha have only 42 minutes to stop a spaceship's collision with the sun and catch the vessel's saboteurs.
To elude a group of alien invaders, the Doctor becomes a human professor and lays low with Martha at a rural English boarding school.
episodes.title: Human Nature

episodes.synopsis: Bookish schoolteacher John Smith struggles to accept the incredible news that he's destined to become a Time Lord.
episodes.title: The Family of Blood

episodes.synopsis: People are mysteriously vanishing in 2007 England while the Doctor is stranded in 1969, forcing him to send codes to a stranger in order to escape.
episodes.title: Blink

episodes.synopsis: A trillion years in the future, Capt. Jack Harkness reunites with the Doctor on the TARDIS, which ends up on the edge of the universe.
episodes.title: Utopia

episodes.synopsis: Villainous Harry Saxon becomes England's prime minister and perverts his position to rule with terror and tyranny.
episodes.title: The Sound of Drums

episodes.synopsis: Martha and the Doctor's worst fears come to pass when the evil Master seizes control of Earth, reigns with an iron fist, and imprisons the Doctor.
episodes.title: Last of the Time Lords

episodes.synopsis: It's Christmas Eve in 2007, and high above Earth a spaceship is transporting voyagers from the planet Sto to experience the festivities.
episodes.title: Voyage of the Damned

episodes.synopsis: With a new weight-loss pill being tested in London by Adipose Industries, the Doctor goes to investigate the sinister truth behind the product.
episodes.title: Partners in Crime

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Donna visit Pompeii in A.D. 79, on the eve of the eruption of Mount Vesuvius.
episodes.title: The Fires of Pompeii

episodes.synopsis: Finding themselves on the Ood-Sphere planet in the 42nd century, the Doctor and Donna discover the truth about the Oods' willingness to serve mankind.
episodes.title: Planet of the Ood

episodes.synopsis: UNIT's newest recruit, Martha Jones, enlists the Doctor's help to investigate a kid genius and his ATMOS system, which is used in every car on Earth.
episodes.title: The Sontaran Stratagem

episodes.synopsis: With Earth choking under the poison sky, the Doctor must stop the Sontarans' threat to the planet.
episodes.title: The Poison Sky

episodes.synopsis: Caught in the middle of a war between the humans and the Hath on the planet Messaline, the Doctor finds himself once again a father.
episodes.title: The Doctor's Daughter

episodes.synopsis: With a 1920s dinner party turning into a murder mystery, the Doctor and Donna meet Agatha Christie on the eve of her much-publicized disappearance.
episodes.title: The Unicorn and the Wasp

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Donna join a group of archaeologists at an abandoned 51st-century library. All they have is one warning: "Count the shadows."
episodes.title: Silence in the Library

episodes.synopsis: With the library darkening, the Doctor takes on the Vashta Nerada while figuring out what links River Song to his future.
episodes.title: Forest of the Dead

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor takes a bus tour on the planet Midnight. Little does he know that something is knocking on that bus's wall.
episodes.title: Midnight

episodes.synopsis: What would have happened if Donna had never met the Doctor? How would Earth have handled the Racnoss, the falling Titanic or the Sontarans?
episodes.title: Turn Left

episodes.synopsis: The return of an old enemy leaves Earth and 26 other planets stolen from their places. The Doctor and Donna search for the whereabouts of Earth.
episodes.title: The Stolen Earth

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of Davros's threat to destroy the universe, the Doctor's companions unite to stop the Dalek empire.
episodes.title: Journey's End

episodes.synopsis: When the Doctor arrives in Victorian London on Christmas Eve, he starts to investigate a spate of mysterious deaths and meets another Doctor.
episodes.title: The Next Doctor

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and his fellow passengers on a bus are transported to a planet inhabited by an endangered anthropomorphic species known as the Tritovore.
episodes.title: Planet of the Dead

episodes.synopsis: While visiting Mars, the Doctor crosses paths with a crew of scientists, who become infected by an alien water creature that threatens their lives.
episodes.title: The Waters of Mars

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor's nemesis The Master has been reborn, and the two battle from the streets of London to the mysterious Immortality Gate.
episodes.title: The End of Time: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: When The Master's plan spirals out of control, Doctor Who faces the end of his life as the regeneration process begins, and a new Doctor is revealed.
episodes.title: The End of Time: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: With the TARDIS wrecked and the sonic screwdriver destroyed, the new Doctor has just 20 minutes to save the world, and only Amy Pond to help him.
episodes.title: The Eleventh Hour

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor takes Amy to the distant future, where she finds Britain in space. Starship UK houses the British people as they search for a new home.
episodes.title: The Beast Below

episodes.synopsis: An old friend summons the Doctor, but in the Cabinet War Rooms below the streets of blitz-torn London, it's his oldest enemy he finds waiting for him.
episodes.title: Victory of the Daleks

episodes.synopsis: The Weeping Angels return! The Doctor is recruited by Father Octavian to track the last of the Angels through the terrifying Maze of the Dead.
episodes.title: The Time of Angels

episodes.synopsis: Trapped among an army of Weeping Angels, the Doctor and his friends must try to escape through the wreckage of a crashed space liner.
episodes.title: Flesh and Stone

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor takes Amy and Rory for a romantic minibreak, as the TARDIS touches down once again. But 17th-century Venice is not as it should be.
episodes.title: The Vampires of Venice

episodes.synopsis: When the Doctor lands in her garden, Amy Pond finds herself facing a heartbreaking choice -- one that will change her life forever.
episodes.title: Amy's Choice

episodes.synopsis: It's 2015, and the most ambitious drilling project in history has reached deeper beneath the Earth's crust than man has ever gone before.
episodes.title: The Hungry Earth

episodes.synopsis: On the most crucial day in Earth's history -- the dawn of a new age of harmony or the start of a final war -- the Doctor faces a difficult challenge.
episodes.title: Cold Blood

episodes.synopsis: Terror lurks in the cornfields of Provence, but only a sad, lonely painter can see it. Amy finds herself shoulder-to-shoulder with Vincent van Gogh.
episodes.title: Vincent and the Doctor

episodes.synopsis: There's a house on Aickman Road, and a staircase that people go up -- but never down -- as the time-traveling drama continues.
episodes.title: The Lodger

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor's friends unite to send him a terrible warning: The Pandorica, which contains the most feared being in all the cosmos, is opening.
episodes.title: The Pandorica Opens

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor is gone, TARDIS is destroyed and the universe is collapsing. The only hope for all reality is a little girl who believes in stars.
episodes.title: The Big Bang

episodes.synopsis: When Amy and Rory are stranded in a cloud belt, the Doctor tries to save them by altering the past of the man who controls the clouds.
episodes.title: A Christmas Carol

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor, Amy and Rory assist the president of the United States in saving a terrified little girl from a mysterious space man.
episodes.title: The Impossible Astronaut

episodes.synopsis: With the help of President Nixon, the Doctor mounts a rebellion against an alien invasion dating back to the very beginnings of human civilisation.
episodes.title: Day of the Moon

episodes.synopsis: The TARDIS is marooned onboard a 17th-century pirate ship whose crew are being lured to their death by a beautiful Siren.
episodes.title: The Curse of the Black Spot

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor follows a Time Lord distress signal to a mysterious asteroid in a Bubble Universe -- could there be another living Time Lord out there?
episodes.title: The Doctor's Wife

episodes.synopsis: A solar tsunami sends the TARDIS hurtling toward a factory on earth where human doppelgangers are used to mine dangerous acid.
episodes.title: The Rebel Flesh

episodes.synopsis: As the solar storm rages and the factory crumbles, a Ganger driven mad by the memories of being decommissioned is seeking revenge.
episodes.title: The Almost People

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor needs an army by his side. As he calls in all his debts across the cosmos, his enemies use his closest friends to trap him.
episodes.title: A Good Man Goes to War

episodes.synopsis: In the search for Melody Pond, the TARDIS crash-lands in 1930s Berlin, bringing the Doctor face-to-face with the worst war criminal in the universe.
episodes.title: Let's Kill Hitler

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor receives a distress call from a child terrified of the monsters in his cupboard -- monsters that are all too real.
episodes.title: Night Terrors

episodes.synopsis: Amy is trapped in a quarantine facility for victims of an alien plague -- a plague that will kill the Doctor in a day. Can he rescue Amy in time?
episodes.title: The Girl Who Waited

episodes.synopsis: The TARDIS lands in a hotel where there is a room for every visitor that contains their deepest, darkest fears.
episodes.title: The God Complex

episodes.synopsis: People are going missing, a silver rat scuttles in the shadows of a department store and somewhere close by the Cybermen are waiting.
episodes.title: Closing Time

episodes.synopsis: As the Doctor makes his final journey to the shores of Lake Silencio in Utah, he knows only one thing can keep the universe safe -- his own death.
episodes.title: The Wedding of River Song

episodes.synopsis: On Christmas Eve, 1938, Madge Arwell comes to the aid of a mysterious spaceman who promises to repay her kindness -- all she has to do is make a wish.
episodes.title: The Doctor, The Widow and the Wardrobe

episodes.synopsis: Kidnapped by a longtime foe, the Doctor is forced on an impossible mission to a place even the Daleks are too terrified to enter: the Asylum.
episodes.title: Asylum of the Daleks

episodes.synopsis: As an unmanned spaceship hurtles toward certain destruction, the Doctor attempts to save it and its cargo of ... dinosaurs.
episodes.title: Dinosaurs on a Spaceship

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor gets a Stetson and becomes the reluctant sheriff of a Western town under siege by a relentless cyborg gunslinger.
episodes.title: A Town Called Mercy

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and the Ponds wonder whether an invasion of Earth is under way when millions of sinister black cubes fall from the sky.
episodes.title: The Power of Three

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor races against time through 1930s Manhattan, as a series of heartbreaking events could tear him away from Amy and Rory forever.
episodes.title: The Angels Take Manhattan

episodes.synopsis: It's Christmas 1892, and the Doctor is drawn out of mourning by calls for help from an unorthodox young governess.
episodes.title: The Snowmen

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor's search for Clara Oswald brings him to modern-day London, where something ominous is lurking in the Wi-Fi signals.
episodes.title: The Bells of Saint John

episodes.synopsis: Clara wants to see something awesome, so the Doctor whisks her off to the rings of planet Akhaten, where the Festival of Offerings is under way.
episodes.title: The Rings of Akhaten

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor and Clara land on a damaged Russian nuclear submarine as it spirals into the ocean depths.
episodes.title: Cold War

episodes.synopsis: Clara and the Doctor arrive at a haunted mansion, where they meet a ghost-hunting professor and a psychic who are searching for the Witch of the Well.
episodes.title: Hide

episodes.synopsis: When the TARDIS crashes, Clara gets trapped inside and the Doctor has 30 minutes to rescue her before the ship self-destructs.
episodes.title: Journey to the Centre of the TARDIS

episodes.synopsis: Doctor Who and Clara arrive in Victorian Yorkshire, where corpses with waxy, glowing red skin are piling up.
episodes.title: The Crimson Horror

episodes.synopsis: When the Doctor and Clara arrive at the abandoned theme park Hedgewick's World of Wonders, they're confronted by the Cybermen.
episodes.title: Nightmare in Silver

episodes.synopsis: The Doctor has a secret that he planned to take to his grave -- but it's about to be revealed.
episodes.title: The Name of the Doctor

episodes.synopsis: This explosive 50th anniversary episode of the long-running sci-fi series reveals that the Doctor has a dangerous past. And he's coming back.
episodes.title: The Day of the Doctor

episodes.synopsis: Drawn to a mysterious message echoing out to the stars, the universe's deadliest species gather. The Doctor must learn what the cryptic signal means.
episodes.title: The Time of the Doctor
